{"author":{"id":"6fe2d7caea518c95e9f8542a2401015ca65f976dfdb6d4e3fa107b0f63c1f1c3"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1460727593,"nonce":"hGT0DpViw68i1lXOoX7nmHkc+YA=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUxNDg2NjM3MjQ=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/720","origin":"github"},"title":"bedtools - Genome file","message":"The bedTools tools were updated recently in Galaxy with some great additions. Some of these updated tools require a 'Genome file', which is a file containing the size of the chromosomes of your reference genome. \nSince the reference genome is associated with files input to bedTools does it make sense to have the user input the 'Genome file' when the same information is likely available in the inner workings of Galaxy? Having the user create and recall the 'Genome file' seems like an opportunity to introduce unnecessary errors.","files":null}]}